-- Conversion of Hungary FX loans could require EUR 9-11 bln from reserves -cbank
-- 
-- Wed Sep 24, 2014 04:45AM EDT
-- None



BUDAPEST, Sept 24 (Reuters) - Hungary's central bank may need to provide banks with an additional 9-11 billion euros during a planned conversion of household foreign currency loans depending on the details of the programme, central bank Director Marton Nagy said on Wednesday.

